All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
IllegalMealQuantityException
An IllegalMealQuantityException can be thrown when either there is not enough meals available to add to a subscription or the quantity of meals to be removed exceeds the quantity subscribed.
IllegalNumberInputException
An IllegalNumberInputException can be thrown when the number from clerk's keyboard input is not a positive number and a positive number is expected (adding or removing subscriptions).
IllegalSubscriptionQuantityException
An IllegalSubscriptionQuantityException can be thrown if clerk attempts to add subscription of another meal for a subscriber that has already reached the limit of 3 different subscriptions.
MainProgram
Driver class with the main method allowing for clerk's interaction with the food company subscription management program.
Meal
A Meal is read from the input file and has a name of the meal type and changeable balance of available meals of the particular meal type.
NoSuchMealException
A NoSuchMealException can be thrown when the meal from clerk's keyboard input is not a valid offered meal.
NoSuchSubscriberException
A NoSuchSubscriberException can be used when the subscriber from clerk's keyboard input is not a valid registered subscriber.
NoSuchSubscriptionException
A NoSuchSubscriptionException can be thrown if a subscription from clerk's keyboard input is not a valid existing subscription.
SortedLinkedList<E>
A generic subclass of LinkedList that is used for storing and lexicographic sorting of Subscriber, Meal, or Subscription objects.
Subscriber
Subscriber class - representing a subscriber that has a first name and a last name.
Subscription
A Subscription can be created by clerk's interaction with the program and has subscriber's full name, subscribed meal name, and quantity of the specified meal.
